# Typing Practice
When running the project there's a menu with a select difficulty. Pick a diffculty and begin the session. Once the begins the timer will start for that session and will end once the session end. After it ends it'll show the user their score, list out the words what they got wrong, the time taken, accuracy, and words you got wrong then it'll take you back to the menu where it starts all over again.

## Instructions for Build and Use

Steps to build and/or run the software:

1. Put this neat command into the terminal: curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh  (This allows for rust programs to be runned)
2. Then put this command into the terminal as well: cargo new TypingPractice (This will make the folder along with all the important stuff that's needed automatically such as main.rs)
3. Put the code in main.rs and the other files in that folder will automatically update and change with the codes  you make.

Instructions for using the software:

1. Open main.rs and right above the main program press run so it'll run the program
2. Pick a number based on the difficulty that you want to work on for that session
3. Then copy the words that are shown to you until the session ends and once the sesison ends you can pick the difficulty again

## Development Environment

To recreate the development environment, you need the following software and/or libraries with the specified versions:

* Again just add this code so you can do rust related stuff: curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh


